The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business

 LOOSE CHANGE

 Principal PNB Mutual Fund, in association with Vijaya Bank, has launched a fixed duration three-year plan series. The close-ended, monthly income scheme seeks to enhance the debt component by investing in AA rated debt papers issued by companies with strong business fundamentals. The fund will also invest in equity of fundamentally strong companies to enhance overall portfolio returns. The new fund offer closes on June 5. Investors don?t have to pay any entry load, but they will have to pay an exit fee of 3 per cent if exited before six months and 0.5 per cent if exited after two-and-a-half years.

 ICICI Bank is planning to launch a loyalty card in association with Loyalty Services and Research Ltd. ICICI Bank also has a minority stake in the company. The bank also plans to launch a private label credit card in association with Big Bazaar. 

 Uco Bank has launched a co-branded health insurance scheme, called Uco Medi+Care Bima, in association with National Insurance Company. It covers both the medical and personal accident insurance under a single policy. Customers can choose a sum insured between Rs 50,000 and Rs 5 lakh and include up to six family members.




